[{"Name":"Ember Shen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTDsusnetYbY0hLczH1lIOHCatqSOTs-gwxdOqaEw5c2XKknU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"$1.20. Glutinous rice bun called ham chim peng

The glutinous rice is far too little and oil taste stinky.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP5gJwrmoZgxkQ-PJcRJHvUwAYM7wSZexnhiiLK"],"When":"2024-9-11"},{"Name":"Ivan Teh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5w6w1Nz613H-FTdYMJdrdrsR43y5bcInG5AtU7Oxf59DHDoeK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Dessert Fritter (~ SGD $1.60 per piece) @ Xi De Li.
.
A pioneer brand founded in the 1920s, the fourth-generation owners Adrian Koh, Valerie Koh, and Pathom Koh, set the baseline for accessibility of halal-certified dessert fritters, selling over 10,000 items daily across their 60+ stalls throughout Singapore.
.
They still maintain the traditional hand-pulled dough, and their batter is thin and crisp, shattering and flaking easily.
.
Their 3-in-1 sweet potato, yam / taro, gula melaka / palm sugar infused glutinous rice, has a sticky soft moist texture, with pleasant vegetal earthy grainy sweet savoury floral flavour.
.
The pandan / screwpine leaf infused tapioca is dense but bouncy, with a nice floral earthy starchy sweet flavour. Seems to have a bit more fiberous chew than elsewhere.
.
Their ham chim peng are light, airy, and soft, the red bean paste version holding earthy nutty sweet flavour, the 5-spice version having salty savoury spice notes, both with fragrant bready aroma.
.
The fried banana / goreng pisang is medium thick and ripe, creamy soft with a bright fruity sweet flavour.
.
Their dad invented the iconic butterfly bun as a token of love for their mom, who wanted something sweet and crisp - they still use the original recipe.
.
Their dough fritter / you tiao is hand-pulled, with a crispy texture and bready savoury flavour, best eaten when hot. Quality differs at times though, from stall to stall.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbXcYb1vUgykz_B5-id_Br6NTq3tU1CcBe-ZSm"],"When":"2022-9-3"},{"Name":"Jenny Tan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrylz-AnzudKCj1wiHCcKPny1rKLfau4Nec-NqDTpCakQHE_ef=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Youtiao regularly increases by 10c every year to $1.10 now. [{"Name":"S.W TOH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqv8lAQAjP4uyD8EnKCAQEvKdeI5t0KP4PYEjaLGeAwHJHvI4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"All customers should avoid order food delivery service from this stingy restaurant. Your food is at risk as cold + hot food + glass bottle wine is being carried on motorbikes, pays penny for delivery of expensive food.

All delivery partners should stay away from taking up any orders from this restaurant. Pays peanuts for delivery and wants to claim back $11 delivery fee even though I informed ETA 15 minutes & offered to return back if he can't accept but he still insist that I should deliver.

FULL STORY
There is this male Chinese staff who ordered lalamove courier (motorcycle) delivery from this dining restaurant for collection on 18 August 2024  after 12 midnight after restaurant closed. When I was on my way to collect, I communicated with him on Lalamove app to check if the order is confirmed and i asked what items to carry. He mentioned food and a bottle of glass wine. But he did not tell me of full details that there are many things to carry.

Total there are 4 food bags (there is hot food as well cold food to be separated and 1 glass wine) which exceeded size of what courier can carry. He should be ordering a car instead which it would cost more for delivery.

When I reached the restaurant, it is already closed and he was standing at roadside. He did not tell me this, took up some extra time to find him. Then half way during the delivery around 45 mins, he called multiple times and I told him will reach destination in 15 mins or less. He ignored and continued to talk a long time to me on the phone which distracted me while I am driving which slowed down the delivery time, he says I should deliver straight away upon pick up and tells me his food is very expensive worth hundreds of dollars.

I told him he should put his request in the delivery remarks upfront of cold food + hot food 4 bags + bottle of wine when placing order + require immediate delivery (no additional stops) then I will not take his order. Also I said his food has too many bags and needs to carried separately due to hot food plus cold food, I already doing him a favor did not ask for tip to carry excessive bags. I offered to send everything back to him without charge since he is not happy and not willing to wait 15 minutes but he still insist I deliver to customer instead of returning. He says he will complain to lalamove if his customer complain food spoilt. I told him I pack his food into 2 separated thermal bags (hot 1 bag cold 1 bag) upon receiving not to worry. He did not even thank me for it.

Also delivery address is a security tie condominium I needed time to wait for security to record details, let me enter and press access code to go up lift. This alone took me extra 15-20 mins. His customer (Receipient) of food items did not say anything when I delivered.

In the end this male Chinese staff complained to lalamove support for the slight delay of approximately 15 mins to claim back the delivery fee that is only $11.25 for about 15km travelling distance.

This restaurant is not fair and very stingy towards his delivery partners and even attempt to claim for compensation for slight delivery delay. His food plus wine cost hundreds but shortchanged by calling for the cheapest delivery method - courier (motorcycle), wants fast immediate delivery for multiple bags hot food + cold food + bottle of wine but pays only little money. Then he attempts to claim back for delivery fee. Very cheapskate restaurant. This is hard earn money, since he insist I should still deliver, he should not attempt to claim compensation for slight delay in delivery.

Totally not recommended to take up any delivery jobs from this restaurant. All riders and drivers should stay away as he will create more issues to other riders taking advantage of us over items exceeded and rush before time due, distracting drivers concentrating on the road to slow us down further.

I attached the delivery log as evidence of this did take place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrpKL2s4zBsT_zbOg26A6WRjX7d9zARg0d2MmP"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Shannon Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLz0rC3Ug_V0Tfbe_enp3oelyqpYkCsD1zjUu7JC67ro6QrvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food and ambience. A cosy place with really good service. Ordered from the recommendations of the day which is not on the standard menu. For appetizer we had burrata with white peach and parma ham, for mains we tried their gnocci and wagyu beef hamburger. And for dessert their bacha coffee tiramisu. We enjoyed every bite of every dish, it was a really delightful experience, especially when paired with their excellent wine selection.

I must also complement them on their amazing service. Went there for my girlfriend's birthday, and they offered to add some lovely chocolate writing for our dessert. They were very attentive and polite throughout the entire dinner, filling our glasses and clearing each course for the next item.

To the waiters and chefs of Wabi-Sabi: you all are amazing! Please keep up the excellent quality of service and food, I absolutely love the experience and look forward to coming back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxLNcEAf5DSoKwSaVgxkO1WfKTqI-JT-9i3KWS"],"When":"2023-8-8"},{"Name":"Helloasia Singapore","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1U28VTZx03D58Aicrzp2VkUbC8jC58wb6s1J8jbmj9e4VIbY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went to try out the new wine bar dining place,  WABI SABI Dining, lovely cosy intimate place.
